## MSE = 0.3556 ##
    MSE (Mean Squared Error) measures the average squared difference between the predicted values and the true values. Lower is better. Because errors are squared, larger mistakes are penalized more heavily.

## MAE = 0.3623 ##
    MAE (Mean Absolute Error) measures the average absolute difference between the predicted values and the true values. Lower is better. It is usually easier to interpret than MSE because it is more directly tied to average prediction error size.

